2 HOUSE BILL 1127
1 (A) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1, 2026, EACH COUNTY BOARD SHALL DEVELOP
2 INSTRUCTIONAL CONTENT ON WATER SAFETY AND SWIMMING THAT IS:
3 (1) INTEGRATED INTO THE HEALTH AND OR PHYSICAL EDUCATION
4 CURRICULUM FOR EACH PUBLIC SCHOOL IN THE COUNTY; AND
5 (2) AGE–APPROPRIATE FOR STUDENTS IN ELEMENTARY, MIDDLE,
6 AND HIGH SCHOOL.
7 (B) THE INSTRUCTIONAL CONTENT DEVELOPED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF
8 THIS SECTION SHALL INCLUDE OPPORTUNITIES FOR STUDENTS WITH DISABILITIES,
9 IF PRACTICABLE.
10 (C) BEGINNING IN THE 2026–2027 SCHOOL YEAR, EACH COUNTY BOARD
11 SHALL IMPLEMENT THE INSTRUCTIONAL CONTENT DEVELOPED UNDER
12 SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION BY OFFERING THE INSTRUCTIONAL CONTENT AS
13 PART OF THE HEALTH OR PHYSICAL EDUCATION CURRICULUM AT LEAST ONCE IN
14 ELEMENTARY, MIDDLE, AND HIGH SCHOOL.
15 (D) THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO REQUIRE A COUNTY BOARD
16 TO PROVIDE IN–WATER TRAINING AT A SWIMMING POOL.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
18 (a) (1) On or before December 1, 2025, each county board of education shall
19 develop a plan to ensure public school students in the county have access to swimming pools
20 for swimming and taking swimming and water safety courses.
21 (2) The plan required under this subsection shall:
22 (i) identify strategies to maximize public and private resources to
23 provide access to swimming pools and related facilities for public school students;
24 (ii) identify public and private entities in the local community that
25 could partner with schools to offer access to swimming pools and related facilities to public
26 school students during school operating hours;
27 (iii) identify methods to increase public school student access to
28 swimming pools and related facilities, including costs and transportation, while keeping
29 costs low; and
30 (iv) recommend any necessary changes to policy or law to implement
31 the plan required under paragraph (1) of this subsection and the requirements of § 7–452
32 of the Education Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act.

HOUSE BILL 1127 3
1 (b) On or before December 15, 2025, each county board shall submit a copy of the
2 plan developed under subsection (a) of this section to the State Department of Education.
3 (c) On or before January 1, 2026, the State Department of Education shall
4 compile the reports submitted under subsection (b) of this section and submit a report that
5 includes all the county boards’ plans to the General Assembly, in accordance with §
6 2–1257 of the State Government Article.
7 SECTION 3. 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
8 July 1, 2025. Section 2 of this Act shall remain effective for a period of 1 year and, at the
9 end of June 30, 2026, Section 2 of this Act, with no further action required by the General
10 Assembly, shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.
